<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well, here's a story quite the opposite...

Had formed a crypt group minus an enchanter. Bard pops in and we grab him and move down...
Had myself, warrior, rogue, bard and 2 necros. Anyways, we get down there and begin pulls. We hadn't really spaced the guards well so while fighting they both gang up on the necro before the bard can mes or I can heal. So we're down one person but we keep on. I manage to stay ahead on heals with bard cracksong being twisted when a knight pops in the room and HTs the necro who was lifetapping the golem. Now we're down 2 but we keep plodding along. Warrior keeps the taunt on himself, rogue keeps backstabbing, bard is twisting mes and cracksong and I'm CHing the warrior. Despite 2 more wanderers into the room we manage to kill everything in one of the longest 30 mins I've ever had. 

In fact, the night would have been perfect except that the bard LDed during a golem fight and with the number of resists on stun I was getting (Stun Command is worthless) he CHed twice and the second golem popped. Bard came back in the nick of time but got group bugged because the warrior was zoning from death (I was prepping to Gate myself which was about all the mana I had at the time) so we tried to have them run out but it didn't work. Got another rogue to drag from the door and summoned our rogue out.

Oh, and I scored a Hierophant's Cloak somewhere in there  :D

So the bottom line, as always with groups, is A) know your role and know it well B) don't panic. Half the trains in EQ are from paniced people who could have handled it if they had stayed calm.

------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
Erudite Templar of Prexus
Cohort Chalybeius
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
